fix:
public final boolean inferTemplatedTypesForMethodCallsInFunctionScope(Node n) {
  JSType callTargetType = n.getJSType();
  if (!(callTargetType instanceof ObjectType)) {
    return false;
  }
  ObjectType callTargetObjectType = (ObjectType) callTargetType;
  if (callTargetObjectType.isCtorCall()) {
    // We don't do anything for constructor calls, they have their own rules.
    return false;
  }
  FunctionType targetFnType = callTargetObjectType.getSignature();
  if (!targetFnType.hasTemplateParams()) {
    return false;
  }
  return inferTemplatedTypesForCall(n, targetFnType);
}

issue_description:
See i.e.

/**
  * @constructor
  * @template CLASS
  */
var Class = function() {};

/**
  * @param {function(CLASS):CLASS} a
  * @template T
  */
Class.prototype.foo = function(a) {
  return 'string';
};

/** @param {number} a
  * @return {string} */
var a = function(a) { return '' };

new Class().foo(a);

The CLASS type is never specified. If the @template T line is removed from the foo method, the block compiles with but with the @annotation on the method, the compiler seems to try to infer CLASS from the usage and fails compilation.

